  "prompt": "How can I know who views my Instagram profile?",
  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, Instagram does not provide a built-in feature that allows users to see who has viewed their profile. Profile views are kept private to protect user privacy. While there are third-party apps and services that claim to offer this functionality, they are generally not reliable and may pose privacy and security risks.\n\nHere are some legitimate ways to understand engagement on your Instagram account:\n\n1. **Instagram Insights (for Business or Creator accounts):** If you have a business or creator account, Instagram provides detailed insights about your followers and how they interact with your content. This includes data on impressions, reach, profile visits, and more.\n\n2. **Stories Views:** You can see who has viewed your Instagram Stories. Navigate to your story and swipe up to see the list of viewers.\n\n3. **Likes and Comments:** While this doesn\u2019t show who visited your profile specifically, it does show who engaged with your posts. Regular interaction can indicate repeated profile visits.\n\nRemember to be skeptical of any third-party apps that claim to provide detailed information about profile viewers, as they can compromise your privacy and account security.\n\nIf you are concerned about privacy, you can take steps to control what information is visible and who can interact with your profile:\n\n1. **Privacy Settings:** Make your profile private so that only approved followers can see your posts.\n2. **Blocking:** You can block specific users who you do not want to view your profile.\n3. **Limited Interaction:** Use Instagram\u2019s features to limit comments, messages, and tags from strangers.\n\nAlways prioritize your privacy and be wary of services that ask for your personal information or Instagram account credentials.",
